law.text:
As used in KRS 138.463 and 138.4631, unless the context requires otherwise:
"Cabinet" means the Transportation Cabinet;
"Rent" and "rental" means a contract, supported by a consideration, for the use of a motor vehicle for a period of less than three hundred sixty-five (365) days;
"Lease" and "leasing" means a contract, supported by a consideration, for the use of a motor vehicle for a period of three hundred sixty-five (365) days or more; and
"Gross rental charge" means the amount paid by a customer for time and mileage only.
